               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0161BGY">Golʿa Dabra Bǝrhān Yoḥannǝs/ BGY</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1770" notAfter="1831">Late 18th-century - 1831(?).
                        Za-Manfas Qǝddus is baptismal name of däǧǧazmač Sabāgādis (1770-1831). The
                        name Säbagadǝs (sic!) is explicitly written on <locus target="#117vc">117vc</locus>.</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The name of the original donor has been
                     erased. The name of Za-Manfas Qǝddus (the baptismal name of däǧǧazmač
                     Sabāgādis), as well as of his father Walda Lǝʿul and mother Walatta Ṣǝyon, is
                     written in the main or secondary hand, in the supplication formulas over the
                     erasures (e.g., <locus target="#2rb">2rb</locus>, 3rbc, 5vc, 6ra; s. also
                     <locus target="#63rc">63rc</locus>). The name Säbagadǝs is mentioned on
                     <locus target="#117vc">117vc</locus>. 
 On <locus target="#46vc">46vc</locus> and 109ra, the partly erased name of the original donor can be
                     reconstructed as Ḫāyla Śǝllāse. The name of his mother begins as Walatta Nǝ-
                     (perhaps Walatta Nǝgǝśt, cf. especially <locus target="#179ra">179ra</locus>).
                     The name of his father may be tentatively reconstructed as Takla
                     Hāymānot.</provenance>
               </history>
